)  1- Syntax/Options  2- Examples of Use                                       (
:1


  Syntax:   CRC dir:afn,dir:afn1,... o

 Options:   C   <-- comment output; add comments if output is to disk
            D   <-- disk output; send output to disk file CRC.CRC
            I   <-- inspect and approve each CRC calculation
            N   <-- do not number the files
            P   <-- printer output 
:2


Examples of Use:

   a. CRC *.MAC L      <-- compute CRCs of all *.MAC files in the current
                           directory; include lines-of-code count in display

   b. CRC *.* DLC      <-- compute CRCs of all files, include count of lines
                           of text and comments on each file, and write
                           output to disk in file CRC.CRC
